# .clinerules — ~/.zsh dotfiles

## What This Repo Is
Personal dotfiles for macOS (M4 Air) and Ubuntu (Parallels VM).
Shell config, aliases, scripts, direnv, git config, and tool configs.

## Layout
```
~/.zsh/
  scripts/       # personal shell scripts (sync-claude, sync-gemini, etc.)
  envrc/         # per-project direnv configs, symlinked to project roots
  memory-bank/   # AI cross-session context
  functions/     # zsh functions
  aliases        # shell aliases
  zshrc          # main zsh config
  direnvrc       # direnv global config
```

## Conventions
- `~/.local/bin/` is the target for user-local binaries (migration from `~/bin/` in progress)
- Scripts live in `~/.zsh/scripts/` — `~/.local/bin/` entries are symlinks to here
- `envrc/` files are symlinked to project roots — never committed inside project repos
- `direnvrc` is the global direnv config — do not add project-specific logic here

## envrc Pattern
- `envrc/personal.envrc` → symlinked to `~/src/gitrepo/personal/.envrc`
- `envrc/k3d-manager.envrc` → symlinked to `~/src/gitrepo/personal/k3d-manager/.envrc`
- Per-repo `.envrc` calls `source_up` to inherit from parent
- Machine differences handled via `uname -s` check inside envrc files

## Security
- Never commit tokens, passwords, or API keys
- Never commit `.envrc.local` files (machine secrets go there)
- `sync-claude` and `sync-gemini` are safe — they sync agent state, no credentials

## Agent Rules
- Claude: owns memory-bank writes, reviews changes before committing
- Do not add new scripts without documenting purpose in memory-bank
- `~/bin/` references are legacy — use `~/.local/bin/` in new scripts
